title: 'Poor quality'
body: I bought this badminton shuttlecock because it was the cheapest option available. However, I quickly realized that I got what I paid for. The plastic is very thin and flimsy, and the shuttlecock doesn't fly very well. It's also very easy to break, even with gentle use.  I would not recommend this shuttlecock to anyone who is serious about badminton. It's only suitable for very casual players who don't mind sacrificing quality for price.  Pros:  Inexpensive  Cons:  Poor quality plastic Doesn't fly well Easy to break  Overall:  I would not recommend this badminton shuttlecock.
